Question: You are given the chance to learn how to play a new instrument. Which one would you choose and why?
Answer:
I think I would like to learn to play the piano. It seems like a versatile instrument. You can play almost any genre. It requires the use of both of your hands in an ambidextrous manner. It's requires little maintenance, just the occasional water. And it is a good party skill. It's easy to impress people.